STAR RECORD #3
================================================================================

ID: a7c4c2b9-1b8e-4f8e-93f0-42b4f97e78b9

COMPANY: Seven.One Entertainment Group
ROLE TITLE: Lead Software Engineer / Technical Architect
PERIOD: 2020–Present

DOMAIN AREAS:
AdTech • Cloud Architecture • Software Modernization • Code Quality • Engineering Enablement

BACKGROUND CONTEXT:
When I joined, the TV advertising platform was in a critical state — a monolithic legacy stack powering millions of ad impressions per day, burdened by years of rapid feature growth without architectural discipline. Releases were risky, engineers were leaving due to system fragility, and business stakeholders were losing confidence. The leadership needed someone to stabilize delivery, reduce outages, and create an architectural path toward scalability and innovation. The business could not be stopped and features could not be stopped from being developed as a multitude of stakeholders were involved. The codebase was a mess with all the different patterns being used. This meant issues when debugging the codebase.

SITUATION:
The large-scale AdTech distributed system was a hastily scaled prototype lacking architectural discipline. The monolithic codebase suffered from inconsistent coding paradigms, callback hell, poor inheritance, and unclear ownership—resulting in high bug frequency, slow releases, and developer attrition.

TASK:
Analyze and refactor the fragile codebase into a coherent, maintainable, and scalable architecture using modern design patterns, while maintaining delivery cadence for millions of ad impressions.

ACTIONS:
• Introduced Domain-Driven Design (DDD) to establish a clear architectural structure with defined domains, use cases, and value objects
• Refactored callback-based code to Promises and async/await, improving readability and reliability
• Replaced poor inheritance patterns with compositional design to reduce coupling and improve flexibility
• Embedded Test-Driven Development (TDD) to align QA and requirements early in the development lifecycle
• Mentored engineers through refactoring sessions and code reviews to standardize practices and improve collective ownership

RESULTS:
• Reduced bug report frequency from monthly to weekly cycles
• Decreased developer onboarding time from 6 months to 3 months
• Cut release cycle time from weeks to days, improving deployment confidence and business agility

IMPACT SUMMARY:
Stabilized and modernized a critical AdTech platform through clean architecture, DDD, and compositional design. Improved technical health, reduced bugs, and accelerated releases while enhancing developer experience and maintainability.

CONDENSED VERSION:
Refactored monolithic AdTech codebase using DDD, TDD, and compositional design. Eliminated callback hell, standardized architecture, and reduced bugs while halving onboarding time. Improved release cadence and system stability for millions of daily ad impressions.

