## Achievements

### Achievement 1: Event-Sourced CRM Platform (0→1)

**Core Fact**: Architected and launched event-sourced CRM platform from inception to market using CQRS pattern with NestJS/TypeScript and EventStore. Platform went live with 25 production tenants.

**Variants**:
- **Architecture**: Architected event-sourced CRM platform using CQRS pattern with NestJS/TypeScript and EventStore, enabling real-time data consistency across microservices
- **0→1**: Built web-based SaaS CRM from scratch to production with 25 paying tenants within startup timeline
- **Technical**: Implemented CQRS/event-sourcing architecture with NestJS and EventStore for multi-tenant CRM platform
- **Delivery**: Led inception-to-market delivery of event-sourced CRM platform, achieving production readiness with 25 initial tenants
- **Short**: Event-sourced CRM platform (CQRS/NestJS/EventStore)—0→1 with 25 production tenants

**Keywords**: CQRS, event sourcing, EventStore, NestJS, TypeScript, SaaS, CRM, multi-tenant, 0→1, startup

**Interview Defensibility**: ✅ Can explain CQRS trade-offs, event store design, projection rebuilding, why event sourcing for CRM, tenant isolation strategy

---

### Achievement 2: Event Storming & Domain Discovery

**Core Fact**: Led event storming meetings with all stakeholders to create the domain model and requirements for the web-based SaaS CRM developed from scratch.

**Variants**:
- **Process**: Led event storming sessions with stakeholders to discover domain model and define bounded contexts for CRM platform
- **Leadership**: Facilitated cross-functional event storming workshops translating business requirements into technical domain model
- **DDD**: Applied event storming methodology to derive aggregate roots, events, and commands for CQRS architecture
- **Short**: Event storming leadership—domain discovery from stakeholder workshops to technical model

**Keywords**: event storming, DDD, domain modeling, stakeholder facilitation, bounded contexts, requirements

**Interview Defensibility**: ✅ Can explain event storming process, how aggregates were identified, stakeholder management during sessions

---

### Achievement 3: Engineering Standards & Quality

**Core Fact**: Established engineering standards including reusable Angular component library and comprehensive Jest testing framework, achieving 85% code coverage and reducing bugs by 40%.

**Variants**:
- **Quality**: Established testing framework with Jest achieving 85% code coverage and 40% bug reduction
- **Architecture**: Created reusable Angular component library standardizing UI development across platform
- **Leadership**: Defined engineering standards for startup codebase, balancing speed with quality through testing discipline
- **Impact**: Reduced production bugs by 40% through comprehensive testing strategy and code standards
- **Code Review**: Conducted code reviews ensuring architectural compliance and coding standards adoption across the team
- **Short**: Engineering standards—85% coverage, 40% bug reduction, reusable component library

**Keywords**: Jest, testing, code coverage, Angular, component library, engineering standards, quality, code review

**Interview Defensibility**: ✅ Can explain testing strategy, component library architecture, how 40% reduction was measured

---

### Achievement 4: API Design & Documentation

**Core Fact**: Designed scalable RESTful APIs with Swagger documentation, reducing integration time for external partners by 50%.

**Variants**:
- **Technical**: Designed RESTful APIs with Swagger/OpenAPI documentation enabling 50% faster partner integrations
- **Architecture**: Built API layer supporting CQRS read/write separation with comprehensive documentation
- **Impact**: Reduced external partner integration time by 50% through well-documented API contracts
- **Short**: RESTful API design with Swagger—50% faster partner integrations

**Keywords**: REST API, Swagger, OpenAPI, API design, documentation, integration, partners

**Interview Defensibility**: ✅ Can explain API versioning strategy, how CQRS affected API design, documentation approach

